fields.character_bio: Ron Weasley is Harry Potters oldest friend, with ginger hair and relaxed attitude to school work
The young impression of Lord Voldemort, left imprinted on his old diary to one day unlock the chamber of secrets
With bushy brown hair and buck teeth, Hermione Granger starts off as a friendless bookworm until she forges an unlikely friendship with Ron and Harry
Rubeus Hagrid is half man half giant, standing at 8ft 6inches, he acts as Harry's mentor and friend through out the series
Beginning the series as a shadowy threat to Harry's safety. Sirius Black eventually reveals himself, and after much trial and tribulation becomes Harry's protector and mentor.
The new defence against the dark arts teacher, Alastor Moody joins Hogwarts in Harry's 4th year. But Alastor Moody is not the man he claims to be.

An entity that results in combination of the Wills that Arthur frees on his journey to reclaim the Kingdom. Each addition increases her power and knowledge, as well as affecting her personality.

She is known to lie to Arthur or mislead him to further her agenda. She can also split herself into lesser parts if required

The first Will who escaped its prison and set the plan in motion. it tricked Monday into acknowledging Arthur Penhaligon as Heir and relinquishing part of his Key to him. 

Before taking the form of Dame Primus, it took the form of a jade frog.

Each of the Wills embodied a Virtue to combat the Sins of the Morrow Days. Her virtue was Fortitude

Also known as 'Claws', this part of the Will took the form of a Bear. 

Each of the Wills embodied a Virtue to combat the Sins of the Morrow Days. Her virtue was Prudence.

This Will took the form of a Carp. Its trustee , Lady Wednesday, sought to execute her clause for the will (albeit not initially), before being betrayed by the other Morrow Days. It embodied the virtue Faith.

This Will takes the form of a snake. It embodies the virtue of Justice, which impacts the behaviour of Dame Primus after their union. After the merge, she becomes more obsessive with justice and coporeal punishment, in addition to acting more suspiciously.

Possessing the virtue of Temperance, this Will takes the form of some kind of chimeric beast, worshipped by the Winged Servants of the Night. It informs Arthur that Friday had not abdicated and had laid a trap with a fake Key as bait.

Taking the form of a Raven and possessing the Virtue of Charity, it is far kinder than the other Wills Arthur encounters. Saturday split each of its letters into drops of rain, which caused difficulty for Arthur initially. 

It appears to be the most knowledgable of the Wills, knowing that the Incomparable Gardens were not in fact part of the house proper, it instead being the first thing out of the Void and thus the epicentre of the universe
Representing the virtue of Hope and taking the form of an Apple Tree, Arthur encounters this Will briefly in the Incomparable Gardens

fields.first_name: The Complete Will of the Architect
fields.character_bio: Formed when all parts of the Will combine, it possess supreme power over all of Creation.

The second being to emerge from Nothing at the creation of the Universe, the father of Lord Sunday, the Piper and the Mariner. 

Similar to Prometheus, he is chained to a clock which release clockwork creatures that tear out his eyes only for them to regrow. the Architect forged this punishment for him to last until the end of the Universe

One of Piper's Children, her original name was Suzanna Dyer. she was born during the Black Death. 

She accompanies Arthur throughout his journeys. Arthur promotes her to Monday's Tierce, assistant to Monday's Noon
